sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    
    box rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05) Infrastructure Layer
        participant Splunk as Splunk Cloud
        participant Target as Target Environment
    end
    
    box rgba(0, 0, 255, 0.05) TRIDENT-AI Daemon & Agents
        participant AL as AutonomousLoop
        participant TS as TelemetrySentinel
        participant TM as ThreatMarshall (Foundation AI)
        participant PA as PlatformAuditor
    end
    
    box rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.05) Brain & Execution Protocol
        participant Bedrock as AWS Bedrock (Synthesis)
        participant UI as React UI
        participant MCP as Splunk MCP Server
    end

    rect rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05)
    Note over Splunk, MCP: 1. Real-Time Anomaly Detection
    AL->>Splunk: Periodic background polling via SDK
    Splunk-->>AL: Returns metric & audit log streams
    AL->>TS: Dispatch raw metric arrays
    TS->>Splunk: Execute ML-SPL query: "| apply cdtsm"
    Splunk-->>TS: Return zero-shot predictive anomalies (>3σ)
    end

    rect rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05)
    Note over Splunk, MCP: 2. Parallel Multi-Agent Investigation
    TS->>AL: Broadcast anomaly event state
    
    par Parallel Execution
        AL->>TM: Contextual alert validation
        TM->>Splunk: Query security indexes (index=security, sourcetype=pan:traffic)
        Note over TM: Foundation AI maps malicious indicators to MITRE ATT&CK v14
        
        and
        
        AL->>PA: Verify internal platform stability
        PA->>Splunk: Query REST API (| rest /services/search/jobs)
        Note over PA: Flag unoptimized or resource-hogging scheduled searches
    end
    end

    rect rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05)
    Note over Splunk, MCP: 3. AI Triage & Synthesis
    TM-->>AL: Return IOC & MITRE profile
    PA-->>AL: Return query performance metrics
    AL->>Bedrock: Forward structured payloads & prompt templates
    Bedrock-->>AL: Return synthesized Incident JSON & remediation options
    end

    rect rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05)
    Note over Splunk, MCP: 4. Human-In-The-Loop Remediation
    AL->>UI: Stream real-time agent updates & Final Incident Package
    Note over UI: SRE views glassmorphic dashboard and reviews suggested runbook
    UI->>MCP: User clicks "Remediate" (Approve Action)
    MCP->>Bedrock: Request tool call structure validation
    Bedrock-->>MCP: Confirm schema mapping
    
    alt Execution Flow
        MCP->>Splunk: terminate_splunk_job(sid) [Platform Fix]
        MCP->>Target: deploy_containment_rule(ip_address) [Security Fix]
    end
    
    MCP-->>UI: Stream execution logs & state resolution update
    Note over UI: Render "Incident Resolved" state (3-minute lifecycle completed)
    end
